    "mAP stands for the average precision across all classes.",
    "mAP shows the model's performance across all categories, and the higher the value, the better the performance of a particular kind.",
    "It is specifically illustrated in Eq.",
    "where n represents the total number of categories and AP i represents the AP value of the i-th category.",
    "The frame rate per second (FPS) specifies how many images the object detection network can handle per second."
